# FTR-INITLOAD – Initialize KYC/KYT blocks for existing customers (Salesforce CSV + scope)

## 1. Context & Goal

Initialize **KYC/KYT blocks** for all **active individual customers** from **BDWH**, create entities in GO DB (**idempotent**, SCD2 v1), then **export a single CSV** for **Salesforce** import.
Provide **targeted reruns** via a **scope table** and a **SQL-only reconciliation** (external/staging tables, anti-joins) to detect and fix missing customers/blocks.

## 2. Scope

**In**: All-job (seed + export), Scoped-job (seed + export via scope table), SQL reconciliation (load SF export → staging → diffs → feed scope).
**Out**: Salesforce APIs (we use CSV), PII handling (CSV has none), UI.
**Frozen assumptions**: BDWH and GO are **separate DBs**; CSV **UTF-8**, **LF**; single file on **NAS**; initial business statuses `INITIALIZED` (in scope) / `OUT_OF_SCOPE` (not applicable).
**Dependencies**: **BDWH** access (read), **NAS** (R/W), **Oracle DIRECTORY / EXTERNAL TABLE** privileges, Salesforce team (import + extract).
**Edge cases**: BDWH duplicates, customers missing in SF, blocks missing, Step-2 restart (export), volume (\~400k individuals).

