## 5. Data Model (diff)

* **INITLOAD\_SCOPE**(id, party\_external\_ref, run\_tag, source, status, error\_code, error\_message, created\_at, processed\_at)
  Index: **UX(run\_tag, party\_external\_ref)**; IX(run\_tag, status, party\_external\_ref); retention by `run_tag`.
* **BDWH\_PARTY\_STG**(run\_tag, external\_ref, party\_type, party\_subtype, hydrated\_at)
  PK(run\_tag, external\_ref); purge after 30 days.
* **SF\_BLOCKS\_STG**(run\_tag, party\_id, block\_type, status, version, loaded\_at) *(if loading the extract into a table)*
  PK(run\_tag, party\_id, block\_type).
* **No domain changes**: `PARTY(external_ref)` **UNIQUE**; `BLOCK(party_id, kind)` **UNIQUE**; index on `BLOCK_VERSION(block_id, valid_to)`.

## 6. Security & Privacy

* **AuthN/AuthZ**: jobs restricted to `BATCH_ADMIN`; SQL scripts under least-privileged accounts.
* **Secrets**: BDWH/GO creds via **Vault/Secrets**.
* **Encryption**: NAS under IT control; CSV **no PII** (IDs/types only).
* **STRIDE**:

  * **T**: RBAC, dedicated svc accounts.
  * **R**: `.tmp → rename` pattern, SHA-256 checksum logged.
  * **R**: JSON logs with `runTag`, script audit.
  * **I**: no PII, NAS ACLs.
  * **D**: BDWH throttling, NAS quotas.
  * **E**: Oracle DIRECTORY/EXTERNAL TABLE minimal grants.

## 7. Observability

* **JSON logs**: step/chunk (`runTag`, `scopeSize`, `hydrated`, `processed`, `skippedDuplicates`, `errors`, `csvPathTmp`, `csvPathFinal`, `rowsWritten`, `durationMs`).
* **Metrics**: `batch_items_processed_total`, `batch_items_failed_total{step}`, `batch_duration_seconds`, `csv_bytes_written`, `bdwh_batches_total`.
* **Traces**: spans per step (B0/B1/B2), `runTag` correlation.
* **Alerts**: step failure, error rate > threshold, missing final CSV, recon diffs > threshold.

## 8. Testing & Acceptance (macro)

* **Unit**: processor/writer (idempotent upsert, status mapping).
* **Integration**: multi-DataSource (mock BDWH), unique constraints, SkipPolicy for duplicates.
* **E2E**: full Scoped job (small scope), CSV export (tmp pattern), Step-2 restart.
* **Performance**: 400k individuals → within weekend window; BDWH batch size tuned.
* **Security**: RBAC jobs, no secrets in logs, NAS permissions.
* **Non-regression**: seed rerunnable without duplicates; reconciliation properly feeds scope.

